# Project Architecture

## Identity
This is "Kata Framework" (Headless, Media-First Text Adventure Engine).

## Monorepo
We use Bun workspaces. `packages/kata-core` is the engine (No React allowed). `packages/kata-react` is the UI adapter.

## Tech Stack
TypeScript, Zustand (Immer), Unified/Remark (Parsing), Zod.

## Constraints
NEVER import react inside kata-core. NEVER access window inside kata-core.

## Security
Code Execution: NEVER use eval(). Always use new Function with a restricted context for user logic. All logic evaluation must happen in src/runtime/evaluator.ts.

## Game State Management
Game State must be managed via a Factory Pattern to ensure isolation. Use `createGameStore(initialCtx)` to create fresh store instances.

## Engine Lifecycle
The Engine must emit pure KSON (Kata Serialized Object Notation) signals (update, end) and never directly mutate the DOM. All scene transitions must pass through the store actions. All engine outputs must be valid KSONFrame objects.

## Testing
Use bun test.
